@node "Intr" "The Dynamic DNS Project"

        Free Dynamic DNS, Mail (SMTP) & Web (HTTP) Forwarding

Webworks Pte Ltd, Singapore, is pleased to announce free public use of
its IP Registry servers utilising our DDNS System software.

Currently, Linux, HP/UX, Digital Unix, Amiga, OS/2, Windows 95 and NT
clients are provided for update of the public IP Registry database.
Other platforms will be supported soon.

The Amiga version is compiled by Bert Vortman <animal@casema.net>.

Dynamic DNS allows everyone and anyone to have a hostname such as
cool.ddns.org  so that others can connect directly to their machine for
applications like FTP, WWW etc. No more hunting for that elusive IP
whenever you dial up your ISP!

The basic services of the Dynamic DNS project are free. For some
advanced services a small fee has to be payed for maintenance.

There are no restrictions for non-profit/personal uses and most
commercial uses, though we would like to be informed in the latter
case.

For more information, please feel free to visit:
http://www.ddns.org

To contact us:

Webworks Pte Ltd
103A, Geylang Road,
Singapore 389212
Tel: (65) 9677-6445
Fax: (65)  743-0692
http://www.ddns.org

Feedback to:
info@ddns.org

Thanks.

@endnode

@node "Reqs" "Requirements"

To use the IRQuery program, you need to following programs and
libraries:

* Amitcp v4.x, Miami or Netconnect
* Ixemul library v47.x

And of course an Internet account! :-)

@endnode

